  <user-story>
    <as-a>user (viewer or maker)</as-a>
    <i-want>to control which notifications I receive and through which channels</i-want>
    <so-that>I only get alerts that matter to me without notification fatigue</so-that>
  </user-story>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion id="ac1">User can enable/disable notifications globally (push, email, in-app) with immediate effect across all notification types.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac2">User can configure per-notification-type preferences for each channel (e.g., push for auction_won but email for shipping_reminder).</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac3">User can set quiet hours (start time, end time, days of week) to suppress non-critical notifications during specified periods.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac4">**RELIABILITY CRITICAL**: Preference changes sync to server immediately with optimistic UI updates and rollback on failure.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac5">Critical notifications (payment_received, auction_won) bypass quiet hours and cannot be disabled to protect business operations.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac6">Notification preferences accessible from both Settings and Activity Feed with consistent UI and behavior.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac7">User receives confirmation when preferences are saved successfully with clear indication of what changed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
